<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q13_v2" title="Q13_v2" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>
      En un gimnasio, después de un aumento de
      <m:math>
        <m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo>
      </m:math>, la cuota mensual quedó en
      <m:math>
        <m:mn>210</m:mn>
      </m:math>
      pesos. Varios estudiantes proponen cómo calcular el precio original de la cuota.
      ¿Cuál de las siguientes propuestas es correcta?
    </p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        Camila sugiere restar 40 al precio actual y calcula
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>210</m:mn><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>40</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>.
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Ese cálculo da <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>210</m:mn><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>170</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Pero si el precio original fuera <m:math><m:mn>170</m:mn></m:math> pesos, después de aumentar <m:math><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> quedaría en <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>170</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>1,4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>238</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> pesos, y no en <m:math><m:mn>210</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        Diego afirma que, como el precio actual representa el
        <m:math>
          <m:mn>140</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo>
        </m:math>
        del precio original, debe calcular
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>210</m:mn><m:mo>/</m:mo><m:mn>140</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>.
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Después de un aumento de <m:math><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math>, el precio final corresponde al <m:math><m:mn>140</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> del precio original. Por eso, el precio original es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>210</m:mn><m:mo>/</m:mo><m:mn>140</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>150</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> pesos. Verificación: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>150</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>1,4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>210</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        Sofía divide el precio actual entre 140 y calcula
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>210</m:mn><m:mo>/</m:mo><m:mn>140</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>.
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Ese cálculo da <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>210</m:mn><m:mo>/</m:mo><m:mn>140</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1,5</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Pero si el precio original fuera <m:math><m:mn>1,5</m:mn></m:math> pesos, después de aumentar <m:math><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> quedaría en <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1,5</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>1,4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>2,1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> pesos, y no en <m:math><m:mn>210</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        Martín propone restar la fracción
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>/</m:mo><m:mn>100</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        al precio actual y calcula
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>210</m:mn><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>/</m:mo><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>.
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Ese cálculo da <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>210</m:mn><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>210</m:mn><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>0,4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>209,6</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Pero si el precio original fuera <m:math><m:mn>209,6</m:mn></m:math> pesos, después de aumentar <m:math><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> quedaría en <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>209,6</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>1,4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>293,44</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> pesos, y no en <m:math><m:mn>210</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Relacionar el aumento con el precio original</strong></p>
            <p>Si el precio original es <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math>, entonces un aumento de <m:math><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> significa sumar <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo><m:mo>de</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, el precio final corresponde a <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>140</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> del precio original.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Plantear la igualdad</strong></p>
            <p>Como la cuota final es <m:math><m:mn>210</m:mn></m:math> pesos, se cumple que <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>140</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> del precio original es <m:math><m:mn>210</m:mn></m:math>.</p>
            <p>Eso equivale a decir que <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>140</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo><m:mo>↔</m:mo><m:mn>210</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Calcular el 100 %</strong></p>
            <p>Para encontrar el precio original, que es el <m:math><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math>, se calcula:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>210</m:mn><m:mo>/</m:mo><m:mn>140</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>150</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Verificar el resultado</strong></p>
            <p>Si el precio original era <m:math><m:mn>150</m:mn></m:math> pesos, entonces el aumento de <m:math><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> es:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>150</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>0,4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>60</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
            <p>Entonces el nuevo precio es:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>150</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>60</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>210</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La propuesta correcta es la de Diego, porque reconoce que <m:math><m:mn>210</m:mn></m:math> pesos representan el <m:math><m:mn>140</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> del precio original y calcula correctamente <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>210</m:mn><m:mo>/</m:mo><m:mn>140</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>150</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>